{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_41","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"reviewer\":\"codex\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"scores\":null,\"weightedTotal\":null,\"verdict\":\"WARNING\",\"issues\":[{\"severity\":\"P3\",\"location\":\"src/components/space/use-space-members.ts:75\",\"description\":\"useSpaceMembers keeps the previous authorized snapshot when enabled, spaceId, or currentUserId becomes falsy because the effect returns before clearing membersByUserId, actorRole, and isAuthorized. In the current SpaceClient path currentUserId is stable and server PATCH still hard-gates, but a visible caller that disables the hook could briefly keep stale admin UI state.\",\"recommendation\":\"Clear membersByUserId, actorRole, isAuthorized, and isLoading before the early return, and add a regression test for enabled true-to-false/currentUserId loss.\",\"defer\":true,\"deferRationale\":\"Current integration passes a stable authenticated user id and server-side authorization prevents privilege escalation; this is a lifecycle hardening issue rather than a merge blocker.\",\"fixNow\":false},{\"severity\":\"P3\",\"location\":\".flowset/eval-results/WI-035-consult-prompt.md:1\",\"description\":\"The branch diff adds WI-035 evaluation/consult artifacts under .flowset/eval-results that are outside the listed implementation and test files. This pollutes the PR with review-process files unrelated to the product change.\",\"recommendation\":\"Remove the added .flowset/eval-results/WI-035-consult-* files from the branch or keep them untracked/local.\",\"defer\":true,\"deferRationale\":\"No runtime behavior is affected, but the branch should be cleaned before or shortly after review.\",\"fixNow\":false}]}"}}
